@zhili_congress_menu

- @antiwar: German Imperialism is a cruel blight on our nation. We must harshly oppose further intervention.
- @prowar: Japan is the real threat to the people of Asia. We must try to convince the party to support the conflict to stop another Imperialist regime. 
- @neutral: Too many lives are at stake here. The SPD should take a neutral stance on the matter for now. Party members should avoid talking about the war to their constituents whilst we watch and see.
- @principled: We must offer principled opposition against both sides. Japan and Germany are equally as guilty in their actions. 
- @free: We must avoid taking an unified stance on the matter, we shall issue an internal declaration to push for the representatives freedom of choice on the matter.
- @china: What should matter the most is China, not Japan or Germany. The Zhili are corrupt and ineffective, therefore the SPD must consider support for a Chinese Faction and push German politics towards their favour. 
- @ignore: Rather than focusing on social matters, the SPD should actively ignore the war and focus on issues that affect the workers here and now.

@antiwar 
subtitle: This option lets us capitalize on German weariness to the conflicts and wars we've been getting into, however we will have to convince the dissenting factions.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_antiwar += 1;
    Q.zhili_opposition += Q.right_influence;
    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_1 = 0;
    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_2 = 0;
    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_3 = 0;
    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_4 = 0;
    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_5 = 0;
!}
go-to: negotiations 

@prowar 
subtitle: This option is highly unpopular around the party, we will have a tough time convincing them. 
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_prowar += 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@neutral
subtitle: There are some demands for action, we'll have to address them.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_neutral += 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@principled
subtitle: A prime compromise between many differing viewpoints, this is not hard to convince the congress, however some of the more extreme hawks or doves will be disappointed. 
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_principled += 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@free
subtitle: Not hard to get it passed, but after calling the congress, representatives are expecting to come out with a decision.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_free = 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@china
subtitle: This option is seen by many as insane, it is going to lead to a lot of discussion around the party, but we might be able to choose a warlord to support?...
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_china += 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 


@ignore
subtitle: Focus on bread and gas prices.
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_ignore += 1;
!}
go-to: negotiations 

@negotiations 
on-arrival: {!

Q.total_vote_pool = (Q.right_influence + Q.labor_influence + Q.left_influence + Q.center_influence + Q.young_turk_influence);

Q.total_vote_pool_support = Q.total_vote_pool - Q.zhili_opposition;

Q.zhilivotesupport = (Q.total_vote_pool_support);

Q.zhilivotesupport_display = (Q.total_vote_pool_support).toFixed(1);

!}
go-to: zhili-negotiation-menu

hi we're negotiating testt

our support is [+ zhilivotesupport_display +]%

[? if zhilivotesupport >= 50 and zhilivotesupport <= 59 and zhili_antiwar = 1 : Somehow, this has turned out to be a very divisive measure. ?]

[? if zhilivotesupport >= 60 and zhili_antiwar = 1 : As expected, most of the party is supportive of opposing the war, however a number of dissenters exist and are calling for a vote. We are certain to win, but we could try to further discussions and appease them. ?]

@zhili-negotiation-menu

- @vote: Let's bring it to a vote.
- @noopposition: The party has agreed on this course of action. We don't need a vote!
- @favours: Do we have any leverage we can use to tilt the vote?
- @antiwar_vote: We will focus on the potential gains: The March Coalition is big and only the SPD and the far right are possible sources for the anti-war movement.
- @antiwar_concession1: We will promise a "tolerant" party discipline. Officially the SPD will posit itself as anti-war, but we won't force representatives to campaign on it. 
- @antiwar_concession2: We shall concede on a "restrained" campaign: No leveraging outside resources and no non-parliamentarian measures to stop intervention. The SPD will get this war stopped via primarily parliamentary processes.
- @antiwar_urge: We must urge about the timing, it's essential we act as soon as possible!
- @antiwar_uspd: We will focus on a debate around the mistakes of the past. The USPD, the war, and the Ludendorff cabinet that the SPD unwittingly aided. 

@vote
choose-if: zhilivotesupport >= 50

WIP

@noopposition
choose-if: zhilivotesupport >= 75

WIP

@favours

WIP

@antiwar_concession1
subtitle: This will move our party towards a more decentralized model and make it hard for us to rally any dissenting representatives to a vote in the future.
view-if: zhili_antiwar == 1
choose-if: zhili_antiwar_concession_1 == 0   
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_opposition -= (Q.right_influence/2);
    
    if (Q.zhili_opposition < 0) {
        Q.zhili_opposition = 0;
    }

    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_1 = 1
!}
go-to: negotiations

aaaa

@antiwar_concession2
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_opposition -= (Q.right_influence/2);
    
    if (Q.zhili_opposition < 0) {
        Q.zhili_opposition = 0;
    }

    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_2 = 1

!}
subtitle: This concession is already well liked by some of the pragmatists, though it can legitimize this course of action with moderates, possibly making it harder to pull out in the future without a good reason.
view-if: zhili_antiwar == 1
choose-if: zhili_antiwar_concession_2 == 0   
go-to: negotiations

@antiwar_urge 
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_opposition -= (Q.right_influence/2);
    
    if (Q.zhili_opposition < 0) {
        Q.zhili_opposition = 0;
    }
    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_3 = 1

!}
subtitle: If we can't make the best out of an early congress, this rethoric will very quickly lead this decision to be seen as a mistake in hindsight.
choose-if: zhili_antiwar_concession_3 == 0   
view-if: zhili_antiwar == 1
go-to: negotiations

@antiwar_vote
on-arrival: {!
    Q.zhili_opposition -= (Q.right_influence/2);
    
    if (Q.zhili_opposition < 0) {
        Q.zhili_opposition = 0;
    }

    Q.zhili_antiwar_concession_4 = 1

!}
subtitle: As the main opposition party, this is a consistent approach that's easy to convince the dissenters and could bring actual gains, however, if we fail to make inroads into the March Coalition, it might backfire.
view-if: zhili_antiwar == 1
choose-if: zhili_antiwar_concession_4 == 0
go-to: negotiations

